{"title_page": "Megan Boone", "text_new": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Megan Boone\n| image = The Blacklist - Megan Boone (cropped).jpg\n| imagesize = \n| caption = Boone at the 2013 [[San Diego Comic-Con International|San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1983|4|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Petoskey, Michigan]], U.S.\n| nationality = United States\n| partner = Dan Estabrook\n| children = 1\n| known_for=''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]''\n| occupation = Actress\n| yearsactive = 2001\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Megan Boone''' (born April 29, 1983) is an American actress. She is best known for her role as [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] agent and profiler [[List of The Blacklist characters|Elizabeth Keen]] on the [[NBC]] drama series ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wkyc.com/article/entertainment/television/megan-boone-star-of-nbcs-the-blacklist-sits-down-with-betsy-kling/95-2e802344-8e06-4de7-b592-49f4559c0830|title=Megan Boone, star of NBC's 'The Blacklist', sits down with Betsy Kling|website=WKYC|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/the-blacklist-season-6-episode-12-recap/|title=The Blacklist Gets the Band Back Together {{!}} TV Guide|date=2019-03-22|website=TVGuide.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref> She is a regular on ''[[Law & Order: LA]]'' and ''[[Blue Bloods (TV series)|Blue Bloods]]'' and has appeared in films such as ''[[My Bloody Valentine 3D]]'' (2009) and ''[[Step Up Revolution]]'' (2012).\n\n==Early life and education==\nBoone was born in [[Petoskey, Michigan]] and raised in [[The Villages, Florida]]. Her parents relocated there when she was a child to be closer to her grandparents.<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Rorke |first1=Robert |last2=Getlen |first2=Larry |last3=Seibel |first3=Deborah Starr |date=September 8, 2013 |title=Actors to watch this fall |url=https://nypost.com/2013/09/08/actors-to-watch-this-fall/ |newspaper=[[New York Post]] | accessdate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref> Her grandfather, [[H. Gary Morse]], was the developer of The Villages; and her mother, Jennifer Parr, is the Director of Sales.<ref name=\"villages-news.com\">{{Cite news |date=September 30, 2013 |title=NBC\u2019s new hit show \u2018The Blacklist\u2019 stars talented local actress Megan Boone |newspaper=Villages-News |url=http://www.villages-news.com/local-girl-megan-boone-wins-positive-reviews-nbcs-new-show-blacklist/ |accessdate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref> Boone says that she was \"hooked\" on acting at age seven when her grandparents took her to [[New York City|New York]] to see a [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] play starring [[Nathan Lane]].<ref>Per Boone's remarks during appearance on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' (January 16, 2018).</ref>\n\nBoone studied acting as a student at [[Belleview High School]], where she graduated in 2001.<ref name=\"villages-news.com\"/> In 2005, she graduated from [[Florida State University]]'s [[Florida State University College of Visual Arts, Theatre and Dance|School of Theatre]] with a [[Bachelor of Fine Arts]] (BFA) in Acting.<ref>{{cite web |title=Alum to Star in New NBC Series |date=September 6, 2013 |url=http://theatre.fsu.edu/News/Top-Stories/Alum-to-Star-in-New-NBC-Series |archive-url=https://archive.is/20131008011938/http://theatre.fsu.edu/News/Top-Stories/Alum-to-Star-in-New-NBC-Series |url-status=dead |archive-date=October 8, 2013 |publisher=[[Florida State University]] |accessdate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref> Boone studied with [[Jane Alexander]] and [[Edwin Sherin]] at the [[Asolo Repertory Theatre]] and workshopped with playwright [[Mark Medoff]].<ref name=\"nbcbio\">{{cite web |title=Megan Boone Bio &#124; Elizabeth Keen &#124; The Blacklist &#124 |url=http://www.nbc.com/the-blacklist/about/bio/cast/megan-boone/744975/ |publisher=[[NBC]] |accessdate=October 11, 2013 }}</ref> Boone credits Alexander with influencing her to continue acting though she considered quitting early in her career.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{Cite news |date=September 30, 2013 |title=NBC\u2019s new hit show \u2018The Blacklist\u2019 stars talented local actress Megan Boone |newspaper=Villages-News |url=http://www.villages-news.com/local-girl-megan-boone-wins-positive-reviews-nbcs-new-show-blacklist/ |accessdate=April 27, 2015 }}</ref> In late 2017, Boone began studying for an MBA in [[Sustainability science|Sustainability]] from [[Bard College]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://grist.org/article/the-blacklists-megan-boone-has-a-new-target-climate-change/|title=The Blacklist\u2019s Megan Boone has a new target: climate change|date=2017-09-26|work=Grist|access-date=2017-09-30|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nBoone starred in the 2007 [[Los Angeles]] debut of the [[Charles L. Mee]] play ''Limonade Tous Les Jours'' and won two [[LA Weekly Theater Award]]s for her performance.<ref>{{Cite news |first=Terry |last=Morgan |date=August 5, 2007 |title=Review: \u2018Limonade Tous Les Jours\u2019 |url=https://variety.com/2007/legit/reviews/limonade-tous-les-jours-1200557404/ |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=October 11, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |first=Steven Leigh |last=Morris |date=April 8, 2008 |title=The 29th Annual L.A. Weekly Theater Awards |url=http://www.laweekly.com/2008-04-10/stage/rock-amp-rollin-8217/full/ |newspaper=[[LA Weekly]] |accessdate=October 11, 2013 }}</ref> Boone made her feature film debut in the horror film ''[[My Bloody Valentine 3D]]'' (2009),<ref>{{cite web |first=Alyse |last=Wax |date=January 16, 2009 |title='My Bloody Valentine 3D' Gives Us a Boone! |url=http://www.fearnet.com/news/news-article/my-bloody-valentine-3d-gives-us-boone |publisher=[[Fearnet]] |accessdate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref> followed by a supporting role in ''[[Sex and the City 2]]'' in 2010. During 2010 in her year in television, she portrayed Junior Deputy District Attorney [[Lauren Stanton]] in the short-lived [[NBC]] series ''[[Law & Order: LA]]''. That same year, Boone made her directorial debut with the independent film ''Eggshells for Soil'', portions of which were shot in her hometown, [[The Villages, Florida]].<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/> She has also appeared in ''[[Step Up Revolution]]'' (2012), the fourth film in the [[Step Up (film series)|''Step Up'' series]].<ref>{{Cite news |first=Justin |last=Lowe |date=July 25, 2012 |title=Step Up Revolution: Film Review |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/step-up-revolution-film-review-353542 |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=October 13, 2013 }}</ref>\n\nBoone would later receive a starring role in the independent drama ''Leave Me Like You Found Me'' (2012),<ref>{{Cite news |first=Dan |last=Schoenbrun |date=March 12, 2012 |title=Five Questions with ''Leave Me Like You Found Me'' Director Adele Romanski |magazine=[[Filmmaker (magazine)|Filmmaker]] |url=http://filmmakermagazine.com/41715-five-questions-with-leave-me-like-you-found-me-director-adele-romanski/ |accessdate=October 13, 2013 }}</ref> for which she won the [[Gen Art Film Festival]] Award for Best Actress.<ref name=\"nbcbio\"/> She had a recurring role on the [[CBS]] police drama series ''[[Blue Bloods (TV series)|Blue Bloods]]'' in 2013,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/10/blue-bloods-megan-boone-to-sub-for-jennifer-esposito-as-dannys-partner/|title=Megan Boone To Do Arc On \u2018Blue Bloods\u2019 As Danny\u2019s Partner, Subs For Jennifer Esposito|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=October 25, 2012|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=2013-05-22}}</ref> followed by her starring role of [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] agent Elizabeth Keen in the NBC series ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]'' the same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/03/megan-boone-cast-as-female-lead-in-nbc-pilot-blacklist/|title=Megan Boone Cast As Female Lead In NBC Pilot \u2018Blacklist\u2019|author=Nellie Andreeva|date=March 1, 2013|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> ''The Blacklist'' achieved both critical and public success, including good [[Digital video recorder|DVR]] ratings scores.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://medialifemagazine.com/nbcs-blacklist-jumps-among-dvr-viewers/|title=NBC\u2019s \u2018The Blacklist\u2019 jumps among DVR viewers|website=MediaLife Magazine|accessdate=March 20, 2018|date=March 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415061048/http://medialifemagazine.com/nbcs-blacklist-jumps-among-dvr-viewers/|archive-date=April 15, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn November 2015, Boone's representative confirmed she and artist Dan Estabrook were expecting their first child together.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/megan-boone-pregnant-expecting-first-child/ |title= Megan Boone Expecting First Child|last=Leon|first=Anya|last2=Michaud|first2=Sarah|website=People|date= November 16, 2015|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> In January 2016, during an appearance on ''[[Live! with Kelly and Michael]]'', Boone revealed she and Estabrook were engaged and expecting a girl.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.accessonline.com/articles/blacklists-megan-boone-reveals-babys-gender-and-shes-engaged|title= \u2018Blacklist\u2019s\u2019 Megan Boone Reveals Baby\u2019s Gender \u2013 And She\u2019s Engaged!|website=Access Hollywood|date=January 18, 2016|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref> \nBoone gave birth to a daughter that April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/megan-boone-welcomes-daughter-caroline/|title=Megan Boone Welcomes Daughter Caroline|author=Leon, Anya|publisher=People. com.|date=April 20, 2016|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.today.com/parents/blacklist-star-megan-boone-welcomes-baby-daughter-caroline-boone-estabrook-t87401|title=Blacklist Star Megan Boone Welcomes Daughter|author=Dawn, Randee|publisher=Today|date=April 20, 2016|accessdate=October 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the birth of her daughter, she is increasingly involved in raising awareness of environmental issues. In January 2017, she launched the CarolineAgnes.org Foundation, which helps provide parents with gift-giving options for their children that are environmentally safe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/entertainment-news/227124/Megan-Boone-started-environmental-foundation-after-daughters-birth|title=Megan Boone started environmental foundation after daughter's birth|website=Xpos\u00e9.ie|publisher=TV3.ie|date=January 4, 2017|accessdate=January 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Elijah''\n| Abigail\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''The Mustachioed Bandit Meets His End''\n| Kate\n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[My Bloody Valentine 3D]]''\n| Megan\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[The Myth of the American Sleepover]]''\n| Kerri Sullivan\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Eggshells for Soil''\n| Teacher\n| Also director, writer and producer\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Sex and the City 2]]''\n| Allie\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Step Up Revolution]]''\n| Claire Asa\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[About Cherry]]''\n| Jake\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Leave Me Like You Found Me]]''\n| Erin\n| [[Gen Art|Gen Art Film Festival]] Award for Best Actress\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Welcome to the Jungle (2013 film)|Welcome to the Jungle]]''\n| Lisa\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Family Games''\n| Sloane\n| Movie released in 2018\n\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[The Cleaner (TV series)|The Cleaner]]''\n| Rae\n| Episode: \"Five Little Words\"\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Cold Case]]''\n| Helen McCormick '60\n| Episode: \"Wings\"\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Harvard Medical School''\n| Nell Larson\n| Unsold TV pilot\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''HMS: White Coat''\n| Nell Larson\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2010\u20132011\n| ''[[Law & Order: LA]]''\n| DDA Lauren Stanton\n| 7 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Blue Bloods (TV series)|Blue Bloods]]''\n| Detective Candice McElroy\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\u2013present\n| ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]''\n| Elizabeth Keen\n| 140 episodes {{efn|Although she is credited in all 145 episodes of the series aired to date, Megan Boone has appeared only in 140 episodes. Because of her pregnancy in the third season, she does not appear between episodes 19 at 22 and her adult character does not appear in the 17th episode of the fourth season.}}\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Robot Chicken]]''\n| Hannah Horvath / Kelly Garrett / Zira / Angie\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[The Blacklist: Redemption]]''\n| Elizabeth Keen\n| 2 episodes\n|}\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|1443644}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boone, Megan}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Florida]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Florida State University alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:People from The Villages, Florida]]\n[[Category:People from Petoskey, Michigan]]\n[[Category:American environmentalists]]\n[[Category:American women environmentalists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Megan Boone\n| image = The Blacklist - Megan Boone (cropped).jpg\n| imagesize = \n| caption = Boone at the 2013 [[San Diego Comic-Con International|San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1983|4|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Petoskey, Michigan]], U.S.\n| nationality = United States\n| partner = Dan Estabrook\n| children = 1\n| known_for=''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]''\n| occupation = Actress\n| yearsactive = 2001\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Megan Boone''' (born April 29, 1983) is an American actress. She is best known for her role as [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] agent and profiler [[List of The Blacklist characters|Elizabeth Keen]] on the [[NBC]] drama series ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wkyc.com/article/entertainment/television/megan-boone-star-of-nbcs-the-blacklist-sits-down-with-betsy-kling/95-2e802344-8e06-4de7-b592-49f4559c0830|title=Megan Boone, star of NBC's 'The Blacklist', sits down with Betsy Kling|website=WKYC|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/the-blacklist-season-6-episode-12-recap/|title=The Blacklist Gets the Band Back Together {{!}} TV Guide|date=2019-03-22|website=TVGuide.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref> She is a regular on ''[[Law & Order: LA]]'' and ''[[Blue Bloods (TV series)|Blue Bloods]]'' and has appeared in films such as ''[[My Bloody Valentine 3D]]'' (2009) and ''[[Step Up Revolution]]'' (2012).\n\n==Early life and education==\nBoone was born in [[Petoskey, Michigan]] and raised in [[The Villages, Florida]]. Her parents relocated there when she was a child to be closer to her grandparents.<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Rorke |first1=Robert |last2=Getlen |first2=Larry |last3=Seibel |first3=Deborah Starr |date=September 8, 2013 |title=Actors to watch this fall |url=https://nypost.com/2013/09/08/actors-to-watch-this-fall/ |newspaper=[[New York Post]] | accessdate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref> Her grandfather, [[H. Gary Morse]], was the developer of The Villages; and her mother, Jennifer Parr, is the Director of Sales.<ref name=\"villages-news.com\">{{Cite news |date=September 30, 2013 |title=NBC\u2019s new hit show \u2018The Blacklist\u2019 stars talented local actress Megan Boone |newspaper=Villages-News |url=http://www.villages-news.com/local-girl-megan-boone-wins-positive-reviews-nbcs-new-show-blacklist/ |accessdate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref> Boone says that she was \"hooked\" on acting at age seven when her grandparents took her to [[New York City|New York]] to see a [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] play starring [[Nathan Lane]].<ref>Per Boone's remarks during appearance on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' (January 16, 2018).</ref>\n\nBoone studied acting as a student at [[Belleview High School]], where she graduated in 2001.<ref name=\"villages-news.com\"/> In 2005, she graduated from [[Florida State University]]'s [[Florida State University College of Visual Arts, Theatre and Dance|School of Theatre]] with a [[Bachelor of Fine Arts]] (BFA) in Acting.<ref>{{cite web |title=Alum to Star in New NBC Series |date=September 6, 2013 |url=http://theatre.fsu.edu/News/Top-Stories/Alum-to-Star-in-New-NBC-Series |archive-url=https://archive.is/20131008011938/http://theatre.fsu.edu/News/Top-Stories/Alum-to-Star-in-New-NBC-Series |url-status=dead |archive-date=October 8, 2013 |publisher=[[Florida State University]] |accessdate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref> Boone studied with [[Jane Alexander]] and [[Edwin Sherin]] at the [[Asolo Repertory Theatre]] and workshopped with playwright [[Mark Medoff]].<ref name=\"nbcbio\">{{cite web |title=Megan Boone Bio &#124; Elizabeth Keen &#124; The Blacklist &#124 |url=http://www.nbc.com/the-blacklist/about/bio/cast/megan-boone/744975/ |publisher=[[NBC]] |accessdate=October 11, 2013 }}</ref> Boone credits Alexander with influencing her to continue acting though she considered quitting early in her career.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{Cite news |date=September 30, 2013 |title=NBC\u2019s new hit show \u2018The Blacklist\u2019 stars talented local actress Megan Boone |newspaper=Villages-News |url=http://www.villages-news.com/local-girl-megan-boone-wins-positive-reviews-nbcs-new-show-blacklist/ |accessdate=April 27, 2015 }}</ref> In late 2017, Boone began studying for an MBA in [[Sustainability science|Sustainability]] from [[Bard College]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://grist.org/article/the-blacklists-megan-boone-has-a-new-target-climate-change/|title=The Blacklist\u2019s Megan Boone has a new target: climate change|date=2017-09-26|work=Grist|access-date=2017-09-30|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nBoone starred in the 2007 [[Los Angeles]] debut of the [[Charles L. Mee]] play ''Limonade Tous Les Jours'' and won two [[LA Weekly Theater Award]]s for her performance.<ref>{{Cite news |first=Terry |last=Morgan |date=August 5, 2007 |title=Review: \u2018Limonade Tous Les Jours\u2019 |url=https://variety.com/2007/legit/reviews/limonade-tous-les-jours-1200557404/ |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=October 11, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |first=Steven Leigh |last=Morris |date=April 8, 2008 |title=The 29th Annual L.A. Weekly Theater Awards |url=http://www.laweekly.com/2008-04-10/stage/rock-amp-rollin-8217/full/ |newspaper=[[LA Weekly]] |accessdate=October 11, 2013 }}</ref> Boone made her feature film debut in the horror film ''[[My Bloody Valentine 3D]]'' (2009),<ref>{{cite web |first=Alyse |last=Wax |date=January 16, 2009 |title='My Bloody Valentine 3D' Gives Us a Boone! |url=http://www.fearnet.com/news/news-article/my-bloody-valentine-3d-gives-us-boone |publisher=[[Fearnet]] |accessdate=October 6, 2013 }}</ref> followed by a supporting role in ''[[Sex and the City 2]]'' in 2010. During 2010 in her year in television, she portrayed Junior Deputy District Attorney [[Lauren Stanton]] in the short-lived [[NBC]] series ''[[Law & Order: LA]]''. That same year, Boone made her directorial debut with the independent film ''Eggshells for Soil'', portions of which were shot in her hometown, [[The Villages, Florida]].<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/> She has also appeared in ''[[Step Up Revolution]]'' (2012), the fourth film in the [[Step Up (film series)|''Step Up'' series]].<ref>{{Cite news |first=Justin |last=Lowe |date=July 25, 2012 |title=Step Up Revolution: Film Review |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/step-up-revolution-film-review-353542 |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=October 13, 2013 }}</ref>\n\nBoone would later receive a starring role in the independent drama ''Leave Me Like You Found Me'' (2012),<ref>{{Cite news |first=Dan |last=Schoenbrun |date=March 12, 2012 |title=Five Questions with ''Leave Me Like You Found Me'' Director Adele Romanski |magazine=[[Filmmaker (magazine)|Filmmaker]] |url=http://filmmakermagazine.com/41715-five-questions-with-leave-me-like-you-found-me-director-adele-romanski/ |accessdate=October 13, 2013 }}</ref> for which she won the [[Gen Art Film Festival]] Award for Best Actress.<ref name=\"nbcbio\"/> She had a recurring role on the [[CBS]] police drama series ''[[Blue Bloods (TV series)|Blue Bloods]]'' in 2013,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/10/blue-bloods-megan-boone-to-sub-for-jennifer-esposito-as-dannys-partner/|title=Megan Boone To Do Arc On \u2018Blue Bloods\u2019 As Danny\u2019s Partner, Subs For Jennifer Esposito|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=October 25, 2012|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=2013-05-22}}</ref> followed by her starring role of [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] agent Elizabeth Keen in the NBC series ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]'' the same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/03/megan-boone-cast-as-female-lead-in-nbc-pilot-blacklist/|title=Megan Boone Cast As Female Lead In NBC Pilot \u2018Blacklist\u2019|author=Nellie Andreeva|date=March 1, 2013|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> ''The Blacklist'' achieved both critical and public success, including good [[Digital video recorder|DVR]] ratings scores.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://medialifemagazine.com/nbcs-blacklist-jumps-among-dvr-viewers/|title=NBC\u2019s \u2018The Blacklist\u2019 jumps among DVR viewers|website=MediaLife Magazine|accessdate=March 20, 2018|date=March 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415061048/http://medialifemagazine.com/nbcs-blacklist-jumps-among-dvr-viewers/|archive-date=April 15, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn November 2015, Boone's representative confirmed she and artist Dan Estabrook were expecting their first child together.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/megan-boone-pregnant-expecting-first-child/ |title= Megan Boone Expecting First Child|last=Leon|first=Anya|last2=Michaud|first2=Sarah|website=People|date= November 16, 2015|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> In January 2016, during an appearance on ''[[Live! with Kelly and Michael]]'', Boone revealed she and Estabrook were engaged and expecting a girl.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.accessonline.com/articles/blacklists-megan-boone-reveals-babys-gender-and-shes-engaged|title= \u2018Blacklist\u2019s\u2019 Megan Boone Reveals Baby\u2019s Gender \u2013 And She\u2019s Engaged!|website=Access Hollywood|date=January 18, 2016|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref> \nBoone gave birth to a daughter that April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/megan-boone-welcomes-daughter-caroline/|title=Megan Boone Welcomes Daughter Caroline|author=Leon, Anya|publisher=People. com.|date=April 20, 2016|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.today.com/parents/blacklist-star-megan-boone-welcomes-baby-daughter-caroline-boone-estabrook-t87401|title=Blacklist Star Megan Boone Welcomes Daughter|author=Dawn, Randee|publisher=Today|date=April 20, 2016|accessdate=October 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the birth of her daughter, she is increasingly involved in raising awareness of environmental issues. In January 2017, she launched the CarolineAgnes.org Foundation, which helps provide parents with gift-giving options for their children that are environmentally safe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv3.ie/xpose/article/entertainment-news/227124/Megan-Boone-started-environmental-foundation-after-daughters-birth|title=Megan Boone started environmental foundation after daughter's birth|website=Xpos\u00e9.ie|publisher=TV3.ie|date=January 4, 2017|accessdate=January 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Fi