|Bilingual (Mali in Marathi), Krishnarao played the lead role\n|-\n|Meri Amanat||1947 ||[[Prabhakar Gupte]] and Shreekant Sutar ||Vikas Picture || Krishnarao acted and sang in the film,music composed by Shridhar Parsekar<ref name=\"Indian films and posters from 1930\">{{cite web | url=https://bombaymann2.blogspot.ae/2014/02/film-meri-amaanat1947.html | title=Indian films and posters from 1930 | publisher=Bombay Mann | date=2016 | accessdate=16 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|Sant Ramdas||1949 ||Raja Nene || ||Devotional film\n|-\n|Keechak Vadh||1959 ||Tara Harish and Yashwant Pethkar ||Manik Studios ||[[Lata Mangeshkar]] sang a duet with [[Mohammed Rafi]] and three solos in the film<ref name=\"Keechak Vadh\">{{cite web | url=http://www.hindigeetmala.net/movie/keechak_vadh.htm | title=Keechak Vadh | publisher=Hindi Geet Mala | date=2016 | accessdate=16 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|Vithu Majha Lekurwala||1962 ||Datta Dharmadhikari ||Manik Studios ||[[Asha Bhonsle]] sang a song in the film<ref name=\"Marathi Songs's Lyrics\">{{cite web | url=http://geetmanjusha.com/lyrics/12496-vithu-maza-lekurwala-%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A0%E0%A5%82-%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%9D%E0%A4%BE-%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B3%E0%A4%BE | title=Marathi Songs's Lyrics | publisher=Geet Manjusha | date=2016 | accessdate=16 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|Tai Telin||1967 || ||Aryan Film Company ||A biopic about [[Tai Telin]]\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Bal Gandharva]]\n* [[Bhaskarbuwa Bakhale]]\n* [[List of Marathi people]]\n{{div col end}}\n{{portal|India|Music|Film}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{cite web | url=http://www.worldcat.org/identities/np-krishnarao%20phulambrikar,%20master$1891%201974/ | title=Krishnarao Phulambrikar, Master | publisher=WorldCat | date=2016 | accessdate=16 July 2016}}\n* {{cite web | url=http://www.ulhaskashalkar.com/#!gurus/zar5q | title=Nagesh Dattatreya Kashalkar | publisher=Ulhas Kashalkar | date=2016 | accessdate=16 July 2016}}\n* {{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0471495/?ref_=ttfc_fc_cr2 | title=Master Krishnarao | publisher=Internet Movie Database | work=Profile | date=2016 | accessdate=16 July 2016}}\n\n{{PadmaBhushanAwardRecipients 1970\u201379}}\n{{SangeetNatakAkademiFellowship}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Phulambrikar, Krishnarao}}\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Bhushan in arts]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Sangeet Natak Akademi Fellowship]]\n[[Category:1898 births]]\n[[Category:1974 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Pune district]]\n[[Category:Marathi people]]\n[[Category:Hindi film score composers]]\n[[Category:Indian male classical singers]]\n[[Category:Indian classical composers]]\n[[Category:Indian male composers]]\n[[Category:Marathi-language singers]]\n[[Category:Indian film score composers]]\n[[Category:Hindustani singers]]\n[[Category:Hindustani composers]]\n[[Category:19th-century Indian singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian singers]]\n[[Category:Singers from Maharashtra]]\n[[Category:Male film score composers]]\n[[Category:20th-century male singers]]\n[[Category:19th-century male singers]]\n", "name_user": "Priya Madhav Phulambrikar", "label": "safe", "comment": "added a word", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krishnarao_Phulambrikar"}
